Quickie ruby script to download a given nasa images gallery, ala http://spaceflight.nasa.gov/gallery/images/shuttle/sts-121/ndxpage1.html 

== TO USE ==
require 'nasa_downloader'
d = NasaDownloader.new

== DEPENDENCIES ==
- linux box
- ruby
- open-uri
- hpricot
- rubygems
- wget

That should do it.

== Questions? ==
Q: How do I download another mission?
A: modify the ruby script, atm.  There's a method in there that has an url to the first page of the gallery - a link to any index page in the gallery will work.
